::Hysteria::

Hysteria sighed as she climbed atop the crates, doing her best to 
balance as she pried off the lids. She pulled out various parts, 
checking each for any malfunctions or incompatability with their 
systems:

"Alright, here's the deal, even if the ship was ariworthy, which it 
isn't mind ya, these parts would have to be recalibrated in order 
function properly with our systems. Or we could do a complete
overhaul 
on what's left of our engines. Either way you're looking at about a 
week's worth of work."

Hysteria turned so she was facing Kluster:

"Whatcha want me ta do Oh great commander?"
